Preconditions:
The input array `arr` must not be null.
The input array `arr` must contain at least one element.

Postconditions:
The returned list `k` must not be null.
The returned list `k` must contain only integers.
The returned list `k` must contain values corresponding to a sequence of pancake flips that sort the input array `arr`.
The number of flips in the returned list `k` must be less than or equal to `10 * arr.length`.
The input array `arr` must be sorted after applying the pancake flips specified in the returned list `k`.